KW  - International business cycles
KW  - Factor models
KW  - Latin America
AB  - We develop a common factor approach to reconstruct new business cycle indices for Argentina, Brazil, Chile, and Mexico (“LAC-4”) from a new dataset spanning 135years. We establish the robustness of our indices through extensive testing and use them to explore business cycle properties in LAC-4 across outward- and inward-looking policy regimes. We find that output persistence in LAC-4 has been consistently high across regimes, whereas volatility has been markedly time-varying but without displaying a clear-cut relationship with openness. We also find a sizeable common regional factor driven by output and interest rates in advanced countries, including during inward-looking regimes.
